-- Warner says Abu Dhabi joint venture worth billions
-- 
-- Wed Sep 26, 2007 12:28pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/26/us-warner-abudhabi-investment-idUSN2622585820070926

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Warner Bros Entertainment and its partners will invest $500 million in a 50-50 joint venture fund in Abu Dhabi to develop films, and another $500 million in a fund for video games, a spokesman for Warner said on Wednesday. 

 Warner Bros, Aldar Properties ALDR.AD and Abu Dhabi Media Co announced earlier Wednesday they have formed a partnership to develop a theme park and hotel, multiplex cinemas, feature films and video games. The total investment will worth "multi-billions" of dollars, said the Warner Bros spokesman. Warner Bros. is a unit of Time Warner Inc ( TWX.N ).